===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Uncertain. {{Han compound|夃|t1=|皿|t2=vessel|ls=ic}}. Meaning of the {{zh-l|*夃}} component is unclear.

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|tbq-pro|*(p/b)liŋ||full; fill}}, whence {{cog|cdm|ब्‍लीङ्‌सा|tr=bliŋ‑|t=to be full; fill}}, {{cog|my|ပြည့်||to be full}}, {{cog|my|ဖြည့်||to add}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}, STEDT). An allofam is perhaps {{och-l|孕|pregnant}}, as well as {{och-l|填|to fill up}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Despite STEDT's suggestion, {{och-l|贏|surplus, profit; to win}} is probably not related, in light of Baxter and Sagart's later Old Chinese reconstruction.

